{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Consolidated 7 specs files into specs/REQUIREMENTS.md, deleted .specify/ and .gemini/ scaffolding","closed_at":"2026-03-01T15:44:24Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":null,"created_at":"2026-02-28T16:48:39Z","created_by":"Paul Gledhill","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"The specs/ directory has 7 files (spec.md, plan.md, research.md, tasks.md, quickstart.md, checklists/requirements.md, checklists/testing.md) from an earlier spec-driven workflow that isn't being followed. Consolidate the valuable content into a single REQUIREMENTS.md (or similar) with sections: Constraints, Principles, Requirements, Key Decisions, Open Items. Also clean up scaffolding directories: .specify/ (templates, scripts, memory/constitution.md), .gemini/ (commands), _todo_resources/ (3 files: vscode-exts.md, fix-wsl-path.sh, win-term-profile.ps1 — migrate useful content first). The quickstart.md content should move to the root README.md (see sister issue).","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"dotfiles-3zp","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":null,"status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Consolidate specs into single requirements document","updated_at":"2026-03-01T15:44:24Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":"mutex"}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Migrated ~60 winget packages, 7 VS Code extensions, and game launcher pinning into chezmoi dotfiles. PR #46 created.","closed_at":"2026-02-28T18:08:54Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":null,"created_at":"2026-02-28T16:49:02Z","created_by":"Paul Gledhill","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"The private repo desertfoxclan/gamer-build-files has rebuild-src/install-apps.cmd with comprehensive winget installs for Windows. This should be migrated into the dotfiles chezmoi structure. Current content in install-apps.cmd: Core apps (NVIDIA, VC++ redist), Dev tools (VS Code, IntelliJ, Git, Docker, Hugo, etc.), Languages (Go, Node, Java, Python, Anaconda, Rust, .NET 9, Ruby), Cloud SDKs (AWS, Azure, GCP), VS Code extensions (40+), System utilities (CrystalDiskInfo, HWiNFO, etc.), Office (via office-config.xml), General tools (7-Zip, VLC, Chrome, Discord, Bitwarden), Games (Steam, Epic, GOG, etc.), Windows Store apps (Affinity suite), PowerShell modules, Registry tweaks. Migration approach: (1) Add winget package IDs to .chezmoi.toml.tmpl under a windows/personal machine type. (2) Create run_once_install-windows-apps.ps1.tmpl using chezmoi templates. (3) Separate into categories (dev, gaming, productivity) that can be toggled per machine type. (4) Handle VS Code extensions separately (merge with existing extension management). (5) Migrate registry tweaks to run_once_setup-windows-environment.ps1.tmpl.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"dotfiles-590","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","so